{{Infobox language |name=Kilivila |region=[[Trobriand Islands]] |states=[[Papua New Guinea]] |speakers = 20,000 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Western Oceanic languages|Western Oceanic]] |fam5=[[Papuan Tip languages|Papuan Tip]] |fam6=Kilivila–Misima |fam7=[[Kilivila languages]] |iso3=kij |glotto=kili1267 |glottorefname=Kilivila }}
'''Kilivila''' (Kiriwina) is one of the [[Kilivila–Louisiades languages]] (of the Austronesian language family), spoken in the [[Trobriand Islands]] ([[Papua New Guinea]]).<ref>{{cite book |last1=Senft |first1=Gunter |last2=Senft |first2=Professor of Linguistics Cognitive Anthropology Research Group Gunter |last3=Levinson |first3=Stephen C. |title=Systems of Nominal Classification |date=2000 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=9780521770750 |page=42 |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Ueb4r6P5wqUC&pg=PA49&dq=Kilivila+language&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiXuMa65NjbAhUkBsAKHSVeAssQ6AEINDAC#v=onepage&q=Kilivila%20language&f=false |accessdate=16 June 2018 |language=en}}</ref> It is used in local schools.
