'''Aimaq [[Kipchaks]]''' ({{lang-fa|قپچاق}}) are [[Aimaq people|Aimaq]] tribe<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.everyculture.com/Africa-Middle-East/Aimaq.html|title=Aimaq|last=|first=|date=|website=www.everyculture.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-10-08}}</ref> of [[Kazakhs|Kazakh]] origin that can be found in [[Obe District|Obi]] district to the east of western [[Afghanistan]]'s province of [[Herat Province|Herat]], between the rivers [[Farah Rud River|Farāh Rud]] and [[Hari Rud]]. Afghan Kypchaks together with the Durzai and [[Kakar]], two other tribes of [[Pashtun people|Pushtun]] origin, constitute '''[[Taymani]]''' tribe. There are approximately 440,000 Afghan Kipchaks.
