{{Infobox ethnic group | group = Lebanese people in Belgium | image = | population = over 2,400<ref>[https://joshuaproject.net/people_groups/13017/BE]</ref> | popplace = predominantly mainly [[Brussels]], [[Charleroi]], [[Brugge]], [[Antwerp]] | langs = [[Arabic language|Arabic]] ([[Lebanese Arabic]]), [[French language|French]] and [[Dutch language|Dutch]] | rels = [[Christianity in Lebanon|Christianity]] and [[Islam in Lebanon|Islam]] }}
'''Lebanese people in Belgium''' are people of [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] descent living in [[Belgium]]. Lebanese people in Belgium are estimated to number over 2,400 people.<ref>[https://joshuaproject.net/people_groups/13017/BE]</ref>
There are significant [[Maronite Christianity in Lebanon|Lebanese Maronite Christian]] communities that reside in Belgium, many of whom are descendants of traders who settled during the 19th century. The majority of them live in major cities, such as [[Antwerp]] and [[Brussels]]. Many them are involved in the trade of [[diamonds]] in the [[Antwerp diamond district|diamond district]] of Antwerp.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/jun/23/diamond-gems-trade-antwerp-belgium Recession takes the sparkle out of Antwerp's diamond quarter | World news]. The Guardian. Retrieved on 2011-06-02.</ref>
