The '''Whitaker scandal''' is a [[corruption]] scandal in [[Uganda]] that surfaced in 2005. The scandal revolves around the Whitaker Group, the lobbying firm of [[Rosa Whitaker]], a former assistant U.S. trade representative for Africa in the [[George W. Bush administration|Bush administration]] and payments she received from the Ugandan government.<ref>[http://allafrica.com/stories/200802041263.html allAfrica.com: Uganda: Country Paid Over $75,000 for a 'Good Image' Letter to U.S. Congress (Page 1 of 2)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Supporters of the work done on behalf of Uganda by the Whitaker Group, however, have pointed out that the criticisms are politically motivated and not based on an understanding of the full spectrum of work undertaken in the United States by the Whitaker Group <ref>[http://allafrica.com/stories/200905050459.html allAfrica.com: Whitaker Group has boosted our economy]</ref>

